Kali-lowmem.notes:
This low memory workspace is allocated 1536MB of RAM.

This Kali workspace extends the Kasm Kali workspace as follows:
  - password-less sudo
  - more packages including Burp Suite Pro, Postman, ZAP weekly, Caido
  - VPN sidecar support when the VPN network device is bound to x.x.x.2

If a network is selected where the x.x.x.2 address is a gateway, traffic will be routed through it. This allows a VPN to run as a container and be shared across containers.

Parrot-sec.notes:
The Kasm Parrot OS Workspace requires libseccomp => 2.5.3 to run.

This can be checked by running runc --version

If you still want to run Parrot OS but do not have the minimum required libseccomp version, it can be run in an unsecure manner by adding: {"security_opt":["seccomp=unconfined"]} to the Docker Run Config Override (JSON) setting above.

NOTE: This will run the Workspace without the docker seccomp sandbox and will significantly reduce the amount of protection that Kasm Workspaces can provide.

Ubuntu Noble with Nvidia drivers.description: Ubuntu is a Linux distribution based on Debian.
Ubuntu Noble with Nvidia drivers.notes:
The Kasm Ubuntu Noble Workspace requires libseccomp => 2.5.3 to run.

This can be checked by running runc --version

If you still want to run Ubuntu Noble but do not have the minimum required libseccomp version, it can be run in an unsecure manner by adding: {"security_opt":["seccomp=unconfined"]} to the Docker Run Config Override (JSON) setting above.

NOTE: This will run the Workspace without the docker seccomp sandbox and will significantly reduce the amount of protection that Kasm Workspaces can provide.
